There are 5 villain players in this season. They are: Ryan and Grace from the red tribe. And Peggy, Dan and Kristen from the purple tribe.

Kristen takes her normal nurse job very seriously, but when on the island, she is very lazy, and comes up with excuses to why she can't do the work. Dan can see right through it all and see that Kristen is being purposefully lazy. Dan is the first to see this. Eventually the other characters catch on.

OPEN QUESTION: How will I portray religious people without being too cliche. I don't want to show religious people as anti-queer. There should be no bullying based on queerness in the show.

In general, most players know what they were signing up for with the challenges, so they're not that afraid to get down and dirty.

During the show, they will show clips of video messages from their loved ones back home. This will be a chance to see relationships.

There will be some "showmances" during the show, where some characters develop 'will they, won't they' relationships. Overall we want to keep these relationships ambiguous, leaving it up to the audience. They may just be getting along very well.
